<article>
    <h1>STAVE OFF ACHES AND PAINS WITH POR&#xAD;TA&#xAD;BLE ER&#xAD;GONOMIC AID</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200905/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-05"><time>2020-09-05</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HOME AND GARDEN</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Sin­ga­pore start-up MaNa has in­vented an all-in-one por­ta­ble stand­ing desk and lap­top case</p>
    <p>(left) for dig­i­tal no­mads and those work­ing from home, who com­plain of aches and pains af­ter long hours at their com­put­ers.</p>
    <p>The Rizr, with ad­justable height set­tings, is said to be also suit­able for those who want to stand to work.</p>
    <p>Founders Man­dara Na­garaj, 29, and Sid­dartha Bu­talia, 35, spoke to a chi­ro­prac­tor last year about spinal mis­align­ments and in­jury due to bad pos­ture while work­ing.</p>
    <p>“Af­ter fur­ther re­search, we found that a com­fort­able screen height was crit­i­cal to a healthy work­ing pos­ture, while also al­le­vi­at­ing neck and shoul­der stress,” says Ms Na­garaj, a de­sign com­mu­ni­ca­tion grad­u­ate.</p>
    <p>Mr Bu­talia, the chief de­sign of­fi­cer, is an in­dus­trial de­signer and me­chan­i­cal en­gi­neer who has worked in in­dus­tries such as med­i­cal de­vices and food pack­ag­ing.</p>
    <p>Info: Rizr will be launched through a Kick­starter cam­paign be­fore it hits stores here. It is ex­pected to re­tail at $279 and avail­able for early-bird or­ders from Sept 22 to Oct 18 at up to 65 per cent off at www.mana.sg/rizr.</p>

